The different added layers: 
- orchestration/automation
- connector
- templates layer
- data product builder

TITLE: 🔥Great debate this week on Damien Benveniste, PhD's post about using Notebooks in production.
TEXT:
🔥Great debate this week on Damien Benveniste, PhD's post about using Notebooks in production. 

The philosophy behind naas.ai is to run Notebooks in production by seeing them as logic gates. 

It means you need to respect a clean & reproducible framework (input/model/output).
This is why all of our templates respect this structure: 

If you press ⏯ and run all the cells at once, it just works.

Thanks Anshuman Pandey for the mention ⚡️🤙
#jupyternotebook #framework #naaslife #datascience #machinelearning #ai #automation #productionoptimization

TITLE: ⏰ When you are scheduling your notebooks in Naas, this is what happens:
TEXT:
⏰ When you are scheduling your notebooks in Naas, this is what happens:

1) A copy of the notebook you are working on is sent to the production folder.
2) A “cron” task is registered in the Naas manager to know when to run it.

Then, the whole notebook will be executed.

TITLE: 🔑 🚦 Did you check our latest roadmap update?
TEXT:
🔑 🚦 Did you check our latest roadmap update? 
We believe templates are the key to build algorithmic decision making. 
= decision making assisted by AI. 

It should as easy as traffic lights to choose where to focus when it comes to decision making. 
🔴 → Red: "something is wrong, move your a** and do more X"
🟠 → Orange: "you are borderline, don't lower your efforts on Y"
🟢 → Green: "you are doing great, keep pushing on Z"

But we are not there yet. 
Join our community slack with the link in the first comment and let's build this together! 

#python #opensource #datascience #jupyternotebook #66daysofdata #100daysofcode #buildinpublic #ai #nlp #machinelearning #decisionscience #community

TITLE: The number 1 problem that prevents organizations to get the most of technology, is going from idea to production (aka live solutions).
TEXT:
The number 1 problem that prevents organizations to get the most of technology, is going from idea to production (aka live solutions).

👉Can you guess what the number 2 problem is?

⚡️Most business people don't understand what it means...

And here's what's crazy...Naas adds the ability to push Jupyter notebooks - the most popular medium to build data projects - to production, to create simple end-to-end solutions that:

1) show that it's possible, 

2) create a foundation to build impactful tools.

#data #business #technology #people #projects #idea #production #datascience #artificialintelligence #marketing #design
